Context:
The text provides information about the services and support offered to first year students at George Brown College, as well as contact details for the Orientation & Student Life team and the International Centre. Here is the extracted information:

* Services and support for first year students are provided by the Student Life team, Student Association, and the International Centre.
* Students can join George Brown's social media communities for the latest news and events.
* Social media platforms include Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, and YouTube.
* Contact information for the Orientation & Student Life team: ask.george@georgebrown.ca and 416-415-2000 (TTY: 1-877-515-5559).
* Students can visit the Social Media Hub for more information.
* Application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, tours, and other information can be kept up-to-date by signing up.
* Contact details for general inquiries: ask.george@georgebrown.ca and 416-415-2000 (TTY: 1-877-515-5559).
* Information on the college's land acknowledgment is available.
* The information contained in the website is subject to change without notice.
* Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
